# =====================================================================
#  PII FIREWALL — nothing personal ever gets committed.
#  Pattern: *.example.* files ship (blank templates). Onboarding copies
#  them to their LIVE names below, which are ignored forever. Your real
#  contacts, sends, and config can never be pushed.
# =====================================================================

# --- Filled-in config + credentials (NEVER commit) ---
config.json
.env
*.local

# --- Live working data (each rep's own; the .example versions ship, these don't) ---
MASTER_SENT_LIST.csv
data/target-accounts.csv
data/suppression-list.csv
memory/do-not-contact.md
memory/warm-leads.md
memory/call-log.md
memory/pipeline-state.md
memory/contact-lifecycle.md
memory/daily-log.md
memory/incidents.md

# --- Generated from templates (produced during onboarding) ---
CLAUDE.md
AGENTS.md

# --- Local runtime / generated artifacts ---
analytics/*.db
analytics/dashboards/
batches/active/*
!batches/active/.gitkeep
sequences/*/roster*.csv
sequences/*/*-drafts*.md

# --- OS / editor noise ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.log
node_modules/
